The isolated reviews converged on two significant clusters, and code inspection found the concrete lifecycle path behind them: a later preparer can inherit someone else’s maker identity and then act as checker; an active PoA can also be edited back to draft by Compliance. Separately, security-package/PoA ownership was placed in `legal_documents` even though the source architecture reserves those models and workflows for `security_instruments`. I’m turning these into executable corrective slices before SH-4/CDSL proceeds.
