+# Functional and Test-Quality Review
+
+No epic completed in this four-slice window, so no completed-epic M## matrix changed state.
+
+- M06-FR-016/017: canonical identity, mismatch capture immutability, evidence alternatives,
+  nondisclosure, action identity, and E2 PostgreSQL races are substantive. Current-maker handoff is
+  partial until 008G2.
+- M06-FR-007/008: F creates protected one-package/one-PoA rows, exact projections, real stamp/notary
+  and signature checks, and retained draft races. Canonical sanction, security owner, terminal
+  activation, immutable consumed evidence, and public generation/activation proof remain partial
+  until 008F2.
+- M06-FR-009: G enforces frozen true subsidiary applicability and exact borrower/nominee signatures
+  with no readiness/repayment side effects. Consumed-signature immutability, action shape, public
+  generation, and authoritative PostgreSQL race remain partial until 008G2.
+- M06-FR-013 remains configuration-blocked under A-101. Later M06 requirements remain with 008H-M.
+
+Test assertions are generally real: D2/E2 assert roles, old/new ledgers, rollback, nondisclosure,
+and races; F/G assert package/checklist non-effects and exact identities. Material omissions are:
+
+1. no later-editor-as-checker matrix across D2/E2/F;
+2. no active-to-draft PoA test or activation race;
+3. no fake mutable-status sanction rejection;
+4. no post-verification signature mutation test;
+5. no retained 008G PostgreSQL run;
+6. F/G positive legal-document fixtures do not cross the public generator.
+
+The independent RED regression supplies executable proof for items 2-4. Corrective slice test
+contracts explicitly own all six gaps.
+
