+The independent architecture review of 008D2, 008E2, 008F, and 008G is complete. D2 genuinely
+restores positive/adverse Company-Secretary authority and legal evidence ownership; E2 genuinely
+adds canonical frozen signer identity, mismatch immutability, nondisclosing resolution, §6.3 action
+identity, and PostgreSQL races. F/G add substantive package/PoA and conditional tri-party paths.
 
-Loan-document and checklist reads project verification metadata only. Checklist completion,
-verifier/remarks/signatures/status, the 008F package/PoA, file authority, subsidiary deductions,
-security, and disbursement readiness remain unchanged. A-111 owns current verification-remark
-retention. 008I is now sharpened from §28.5/§17.4 and the CDSL SOP milestones.
+The review nevertheless proved three High lifecycle failures with executable regressions: mutable
+approved status creates a package without canonical terminal sanction; Compliance can downgrade an
+active Company-Secretary PoA to draft; and ordinary capture can rewrite a borrower signature after
+tri-party verification while the document stays verified. Code inspection also found that a later
+material editor retains the first maker id and can check their own facts through another active
+role. SecurityPackage/PoA ownership is in `legal_documents` despite the source-defined
+`security_instruments` owner, and 008G retained neither its promised PostgreSQL execution nor a
+public-generation tracer.
 
+Corrective 008G2 closes current-maker attribution, database evidence integrity, transport/domain and
+§6-§7 action/error seams, consumed tri-party signatures, genuine generation proof, and twice-run
+verification races. Corrective 008F2 then establishes the security owner, canonical terminal
+sanction scope, exact-draft/terminal PoA activation, immutable activation evidence, and real
